A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Nursing Homes – Direct Care Wages and Benefits and Cost Reports
3 (Nursing Home Care Crisis Transparency Act)
4 FOR the purpose of requiring a nursing home to expend at least a certain percentage of its
5 total nursing and residential care revenue for direct care wages and benefits;
6 requiring nursing homes to annually submit a certain cost report to the Maryland
7 Department of Health; and generally relating to nursing homes.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Health – General
10 Section 16–209 and 16–210
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Health – General
16 16–209.
17 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “DIRECT CARE WAGES AND BENEFITS” MEANS THE
18 DIRECT CARE WORKFORCE WAGES AND BENEFITS FOR NURSING, DIETARY,
19 RESTORATIVE THERAPY, AND SOCIAL WORKER STAFF.
20 (B) A NURSING HOME SHALL EXPEND AT LEAST 75% OF ITS TOTAL NURSING
21 AND RESIDENTIAL CARE REVENUE FOR DIRECT CARE WAGES AND BENEFITS.
22 16–210.
